# Title
Task Execution SOP Compliance

## Description
Each specialised planning agent (vision, requirements, specs, designSpecs, memory, suggestions, info) must gather relevant context via `specsContext`, build its own LLM prompt, and perform CRUD operations on the corresponding files. Document-oriented agents load existing content, call the LLM (fast/deep depending on `PLANNER_USE_FAST`), persist results with `specsManager`, and print chapter-aware diffs. The memory agent regenerates `.achilles/memory`, the suggestions agent maintains `.achilles/.suggestions/suggestions.md` and dispatches follow-up tasks, and the info agent displays the matched requirement/spec/design spec bodies. After all tasks run, the planner prints a summary indicating completion.

